title: For Sale/Trade:  Spikes Tactical / VLTOR AR-15
postcontent:
This is a very nice AR-15 in 5.56 / .223 build on Spike's Tactical parts. This rifle was designed to be well balanced, comfortable to shoot and 100% reliable. I did this by starting with a mid-length gas system and added Spike's full auto bolt carrier and H1 heavy buffer and wolf spring. This AR is a pleasure to shoot.

Barrel is mid-length, chrome lined, MP tested with 1:7 twist from Palmetto State and made by FN. The trigger is a very nice single stage Mil-Spec ACT by ALG Defense. I topped the barrel off with a Vltor VC-A1 flash hider. The VLTOR IMOD stock is rock solid and very comfortable. Magpul MOE+ grip and VLTOR sling plate help you keep a nice grip on things...and if that wasn't enough, I installed the squid grips on the 11 inch Troy TRX-Alpha modular rail. The safety selector is BAD-ass ambi and the charging handle is the VLTOR/Bravo Medium latch. I then topped the whole thing off with Daniel Defense dual aperture iron sights.

This is a thorough rifle; everything was thought of from end to end. I put about 60 rounds through it without any trouble. I just enjoy building these ARs more than I get a chance to shoot.

Feel free to ask any questions. Cash would be nice because I'm going to fund my next build, but I'm open to the right trade. I'm open to cash/other firearm trades or multi-gun trades. I'm not interested in anything else.

I may consider selling or trading the upper only.

    The overall weight of the Milispec 5R is 8.25 lbs. (3.75 kg) and the length is 43.75 inches, or roughly 1,111 mm.

    The stock on the standard 5R is the HS Precision Composite and the finish is a dark gray/black color. Similar to Remington's Varmint Synthetic stocks, the 5R's stock is speckled with green within the gray/black of the plastic.
